Package naointerface.main

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Nao
    A NAO Object is an interface to a real or virtual Nao robot in the network.
    SpeechRecognition
    A SpeechRecognition is a module that can be instantiated from a naointerface.main.Nao object.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BodyParts
    This utility class consist all the names for the Bodyparts of a Nao robot, that are used in the JNaoQi API.
    Constants
    This class consist of constants and static helper methods.
    Move
    This class represents a single, linear move.
    Moves
    This class provides methods which can combine multiple instances of naointerface.main.Move to create motions.
    NaoFactory
    This factory class instantiates Nao objects.
    NaoImpl  
    SpeechRecognitionFactory
    A Factory Class for Speech Recognition modules.
    SpeechRecognitionImpl  
    Stances
    This class consists constants for the names of the staces that are used in the JNaoQi API.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    NoBodyPart
    This annotation is written to mark fields in the utility class naointerface.main.BodyParts that are no BodyParts.
    Supported
    This annotation interface is written just to 'mark' certain Bodyparts that can be used as an argument for the constructor of the class naointerface.main.Move.
